 |DirectedBy = [[Antonia Bird]]
 |WrittenBy = Ben Richards
 |Aux4 = 6.63
 |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2005|9|12|df=y}}
 |ShortSummary = A bomb detonates nearby Danny's [[funeral]]. Section investigate and learn that an American-based terrorist group, "Shining Dawn", who believe the [[human race]] ought to be culled, are responsible; they demand the release of their leader from British custody, or they detonate a bomb in public places every 10 hours. Ruth visits a sympathiser, Curtis, who is targeted, while Adam and [[Zafar Younis|Zaf]] follow leads, and discover there is a [[Mole (espionage)|mole]] in MI5, as both suspects end up dead. They do eventually find the next bomb in [[London King's Cross railway station|King's Cross station]] and defuse it. Adam also tracks down a witness, Natasha Scott (guest star [[Martine McCutcheon]]). Zaf is captured by Shining Dawn members.
 |LineColor = 1034A6
}}
