 |WrittenBy = Raymond Khoury
 |Aux4 = 5.20
 |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2005|10|6|df=y}}
 |ShortSummary = Journalist Gary Hicks witnesses the murder of Clive McTaggart, a high-ranking retired intelligence officer and friend of Harry's who was about to publish his memoirs, which contain government secrets. While MI5 investigate and Hicks attempts to publish the story, a group of people from the government is sent to kill him. Meanwhile, journalist to-be [[Jo Portman]] ([[Miranda Raison]]) follows the investigation, and Adam, impressed by her skills that lead to a major break in the case, recruits her by the end of the episode. In the end, Taggart mailed Harry the memoirs in the event of his death.
 |LineColor = 1034A6
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|List of Spooks episodes
 |EpisodeNumber = 32
